data.title: Dolly Parton's Imagination Library in Ector County
meta_keywords: Dolly Parton's Imagination Library in Ector County
data.meta_description: Dolly Parton's Imagination Library in Ector County - Ector County Independent School District
data.text:
The Education Foundation of Odessa is partnering with Chevron and Dolly Parton's Imagination Library to bring the gift of reading to children in Ector County. Through this partnership, Dolly Parton's Imagination Library will provide one engaging, high-quality book a month to Ector County children from birth to age five at no cost to families.

Dolly Parton's Imagination Library is now available to all age-eligible children in Ector County. Parents may visit imaginationlibrary.com to sign up.

Dolly Parton's Imagination Library mails books to more than 2 million children a month and must place book orders a month in advance. Depending on when you register your child, it may take up to eight to twelve weeks for the first book to arrive. After that, the books will come every month.

For example, if you registered your child on January 6th and were approved by your local affiliate in January, you would receive your first book in March.
